# High-Fidelity Migration Rules

## Process (mandatory)
- Work in two phases: **Plan** then **Implementation**.
- Before edits, produce a short checklist (max 10-12 points).
- After edits, verify checklist and report pass/fail per item.

## No-shortcuts policy
- Preserve UI/behavior 1:1 unless user asks otherwise.
- Use the smallest possible diff; avoid unrelated refactors.
- No placeholders like "..." or "rest unchanged".
- If required source context is missing/truncated, stop and ask for exact files/snippets.

## Execution quality gate
- After substantive edits, run verification commands (at minimum build/typecheck; add lint/tests when relevant).
- If verification fails, fix and rerun until green or clearly report blockers.
- Always list changed files and the reason for each change.

## Migration focus
- Migrate one section/concern at a time, not the whole app in one step.
- Keep behavior-critical timing/animation logic faithful to source.
